[1mcompile-kernel[m
This step is optional. You may now set up a custom kernel for your
installation. To do so, run the following commands.

chroot into your system:
[1m smgl-chroot[m

Unpack the kernel sources:
[1m cd /usr/src[m
[1m tar -jxvf linux-2.6.22.tar.bz2[m (leave out [1mv[m to silence tar output)

Symlink to /usr/src/linux
[1m ln -sf /usr/src/linux-2.6.22 /usr/src/linux[m

Configure, make, and install:
[1m make menuconfig[m
[1m make; make modules; make modules_install[m
[1m cp -f /usr/src/linux/arch/i386/boot/bzImage /boot/vmlinuz-2.6.22[m

Exit the chroot:
[1mexit[m

Type [1mnext[m to go to the next step.
